author: James Ramage
title: Dollar Falls on Expected Fed Delays
text:
The dollar tumbled to a three-week low against the euro on Friday as investors continued to bet against a U.S. interest-rate increase in the coming months.
The dollar slid 0.8% against the common currency, as one euro bought $1.1371, the strongest against the buck since Sept. 18. The dollar shed 1.4% versus the euro over the week.
